    public abstract class AndroidProvider<T extends Data,S extends Data>
extends Provider<T,S>
    Provider with Android-specific thread-safe methods for publishing progress and results.

    Riccardo Mancini

      • publishProgress

        protected void publishProgress(long requestID,
                               int progress,
                               java.lang.String message)
        Notifies about current progress in the execution of the request. The progress update must refer to the whole request, of which this provider could be just an intermediate step. If called from a thread different from the main thread, it will execute in the main thread by using the main thread handler.
        Overrides:
        publishProgress in class Provider<T extends Data,S extends Data>
        Parameters:
        requestID - the request id this progress refers to.
        progress - refer to ProgressData.progress
        message - refer to ProgressData.message
